---
import Layout from '~/layouts/MarkdownLayout.astro';

const title = 'Privacy Policy';
---

<Layout frontmatter={{ title }}>
  <p><em>Last Updated: March 2026</em></p>

  <h2>1. Introduction</h2>
  <p>Address.Hair ("we," "us," or "our") respects your privacy and is committed to protecting your personal data. This Privacy Policy outlines how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your information when you visit our website (address.hair) and use our digital portfolio and reputation engine services (the "Service").</p>

  <h2>2. Information We Collect</h2>
  <p>We may collect information about you in a variety of ways. The information we may collect includes:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Personal Data:</strong> Personally identifiable information, such as your name, business name, and email address, which you voluntarily give to us when engaging with our platform, filling out contact forms, or purchasing our services.</li>
    <li><strong>Public Business Data:</strong> Information required to operate our service, including your public Instagram handle, Google Business Profile URL, public reviews, and publicly posted images.</li>
    <li><strong>Payment Information:</strong> We utilize third-party payment processors (such as PayPal). We do not collect or store your financial data, such as credit card numbers. Your payment information is governed by the privacy policy of the payment processor.</li>
    <li><strong>Automatically Collected Data:</strong> When you access the Site, we automatically collect certain data, such as your IP address, browser type, operating system, and tracking metrics via splitbee/Google Analytics to improve our service.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>3. How We Use Your Information</h2>
  <p>Having accurate information about you permits us to provide you with a smooth, efficient, and customized experience. We use the information we collect to:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Create, deploy, and manage your custom vanity URL and salon website.</li>
    <li>Synchronize your public Instagram feed and Google Reviews to your portfolio.</li>
    <li>Process transactions and send related administrative documentation (e.g., invoices, setup links).</li>
    <li>Respond to customer service requests and provide technical support.</li>
    <li>Improve our website performance, layout, and user experience.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>4. Disclosure of Your Information</h2>
  <p>We do not sell your personal data. We may share information we have collected about you in certain situations, including:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Third-Party Service Providers:</strong> We may share your information with third parties that perform services for us or on our behalf, including payment processing, data analysis, email delivery, and hosting services.</li>
    <li><strong>Legal Obligations:</strong> If we believe the release of information about you is necessary to respond to legal process, to investigate or remedy potential violations of our policies, or to protect the rights, property, and safety of others.</li>
    <li><strong>Business Transfers:</strong> We may share or transfer your information in connection with, or during negotiations of, any merger, sale of company assets, financing, or acquisition of all or a portion of our business to another company.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>5. Third-Party Websites and Integrations</h2>
  <p>Our Service contains links to third-party websites and utilizes APIs from platforms like Meta (Instagram) and Google. This Privacy Policy does not apply to those third-party platforms. We encourage you to review the privacy policies of any third-party sites or services you interact with.</p>

  <h2>6. Data Security</h2>
  <p>We use administrative, technical, and physical security measures to help protect your personal information. While we have taken reasonable steps to secure the personal information you provide to us, please be aware that despite our efforts, no security measures are perfect or impenetrable, and no method of data transmission can be guaranteed against any interception or other type of misuse.</p>

  <h2>7. Your Rights and Choices</h2>
  <p>Depending on your location, you may have certain rights regarding your personal information, including the right to request access to, correction of, or deletion of your personal data. You may also request that we disconnect your Instagram or Google sync at any time. To exercise these rights, please contact us directly.</p>

  <h2>8. Policy for Children</h2>
  <p>Our Service is intended for professionals and business owners. We do not knowingly solicit information from or market to children under the age of 13. If we learn that we have collected personal information from a child under age 13 without verification of parental consent, we will delete that information as quickly as possible.</p>

  <h2>9. Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
  <p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time in order to reflect changes to our practices or for other operational, legal, or regulatory reasons. We will alert you about any changes by updating the "Last Updated" date of this Privacy Policy.</p>

  <h2>10. Contact Us</h2>
  <p>If you have questions or comments about this Privacy Policy, please contact us via our <a href="/contact">Contact page</a>.</p>
</Layout>
